-collision stellar populations can reproduce the B-V and V-K colors of the\nCartwheel's nucleus+inner ring. We find that an additional 10-Myr-old burst of\nstar formation in the nuclear regions, along with the visual extinction of 1.3\nmag, might be responsible for the peculiar colors of the Cartwheel's nucleus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Nov 2001 13:15:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
